          "IT and digital: AI, IoT, cybersecurity, blockchain, quantum computing",
          "Biotechnology: GM crops, gene editing (CRISPR), stem cells, bioethics",
          "Nanotechnology: medical, material, energy applications",
          "Defence technology: missiles (Agni, BrahMos), drones, indigenous weapons",
          "Issues relating to Intellectual Property Rights: patents, TRIPS, compulsory licensing",
          "Developing new technology: innovation ecosystem, Atal Innovation Mission"
        ]},
        { name: "Environment, Biodiversity & Conservation", topics: [
          "Conservation of biodiversity: in-situ and ex-situ methods",
          "Environmental pollution and degradation: air, water, soil, marine",
          "Environmental impact assessment: EIA notification, public hearing, challenges",
          "Climate change: causes, impacts, India's NDCs, Paris Agreement commitments",
          "Carbon markets, climate finance, green bonds, REDD+",
          "Renewable energy: solar, wind, biomass, hydrogen — targets and progress",
          "Waste management: solid, plastic, e-waste, biomedical — rules and implementation",
          "Forest conservation: FCA, compensatory afforestation, CAMPA",
          "Wildlife conservation: WPA 1972, Project Tiger, human-wildlife conflict",
          "Wetlands: Ramsar Convention, mangroves, coral bleaching",
          "Environmental governance: NGT, MoEFCC, CPCB/SPCB"
        ]},
        { name: "Disaster Management", topics: [
          "Disaster and disaster management: types (natural, man-made, biological)",
          "DM Act 2005: NDMA, SDMA, DDMA, NDRF — three-tier framework",
          "DM cycle: prevention, mitigation, preparedness, response, recovery, rehabilitation",
          "Sendai Framework 2015-2030: priorities, targets, India's commitments",
          "CDRI (Coalition for Disaster Resilient Infrastructure)",
          "Early warning systems: IMD, INCOIS, CAP, EWEA",
          "Community-based disaster management (CBDM): models, Odisha transformation",
          "Disaster finance: SDRF, NDRF (fund), PM's 10-Point Agenda"
        ]},
        { name: "Internal Security", topics: [
          "Linkages between development and spread of extremism",
          "Role of external state and non-state actors in security challenges",
          "Challenges to internal security through communication networks",
          "Role of media and social networking sites in security challenges",
          "Basics of cyber security: CERT-In, NCIIPC, IT Act, DPDP Act",
          "Money laundering and its prevention: PMLA, FATF, hawala",
          "Security challenges in border areas: smart fencing, infiltration, smuggling",
          "Linkages of organized crime with terrorism",
          "Various security forces and agencies: BSF, CRPF, ITBP, SSB, AR, NIA, NSG, RAW",
          "Left Wing Extremism: causes, SAMADHAN doctrine, affected areas",
          "Insurgency in North-East: groups, peace accords, AFSPA",
          "Coastal and maritime security: Indian Navy, Coast Guard, Sagarmala"
        ]}
      ]
    },
    {
      id: "mains-gs4", stage: "mains",
      title: "GS Paper 4 — Ethics, Integrity & Aptitude",
      short: "GS 4",
      color: "#854d0e", marks: 250,
      sections: [
        { name: "Ethics & Human Interface", topics: [
          "Essence, determinants, and consequences of Ethics in human actions",
          "Dimensions of ethics: meta-ethics, normative ethics, applied ethics",
          "Ethics in private and public relationships",
          "Human Values: lessons from lives of great leaders, reformers, administrators",
          "Role of family, society, and educational institutions in inculcating values",
          "Ethical theories: virtue ethics, deontology (Kant), consequentialism (Mill), Rawls",
          "Indian ethical thinkers: Gandhi, Vivekananda, Ambedkar, Kautilya, Tagore, Aurobindo",
          "Western ethical thinkers: Socrates, Plato, Aristotle, Kant, Bentham, Rawls, Singer"
        ]},
        { name: "Attitude, Aptitude & Emotional Intelligence", topics: [
          "Attitude: content, structure, function; influence on thought and behaviour",
          "Moral and political attitudes; formation, change, cognitive dissonance",
          "Social influence and persuasion: conformity, obedience, groupthink",
          "Aptitude and foundational values for Civil Service",
          "Integrity, impartiality, non-partisanship, objectivity",
          "Dedication to public service, empathy, tolerance, compassion towards weaker sections",
          "Emotional intelligence: concept (Goleman's model), components, self-awareness",
          "Utilities and application of Emotional Intelligence in administration and governance",
          "EI in leadership: managing stress, conflict resolution, team building"
        ]},
        { name: "Public/Civil Service Values & Ethics in Administration", topics: [
          "Public/Civil service values: neutrality, anonymity, commitment, accountability",
          "Ethics in Public administration: status and problems",
          "Ethical concerns and dilemmas in government and private institutions",
          "Laws, rules, regulations and conscience as sources of ethical guidance",
          "Accountability and ethical governance: mechanisms, limitations",
          "Strengthening of ethical and moral values in governance",
          "Ethical issues in international relations and funding",
          "Corporate governance: principles, CSR, board ethics, stakeholder theory"
        ]},
        { name: "Probity in Governance", topics: [
          "Concept of public service; philosophical basis of governance and probity",
          "Information sharing and transparency in government",
          "Right to Information: provisions, impact, limitations",
          "Codes of Ethics and Codes of Conduct: differences, enforcement",
          "Citizen's Charters: Sevottam model, effectiveness, limitations",
          "Work culture: punctuality, accountability, team spirit",
          "Quality of service delivery: benchmarking, citizen satisfaction",
          "Utilization of public funds: fiduciary responsibility, audit",
          "Challenges of corruption: causes, consequences, remedies",
          "Vigilance and anti-corruption: CVC, Lokpal, whistleblower protection",
          "Social audit: concept, RTI-based, MGNREGA social audits"
        ]},
        { name: "Case Studies on Ethics", topics: [
          "Case studies testing attitude, values, and aptitude",
          "Ethical dilemmas in public administration: competing duties",
          "Decision-making in complex scenarios with multiple stakeholders",
          "Balancing competing interests: development vs environment, rights vs security",
          "Handling pressure from politicians, superiors, media, public",
          "Whistleblowing: when to report, protection, personal cost",
          "Ensuring fairness, justice, and inclusivity in governance",
          "Leadership in crisis: natural disasters, communal tensions, pandemic",
          "Implementing citizen-centric policies against bureaucratic inertia",
          "Upholding constitutional values in day-to-day administration",
          "Conflict resolution: negotiation, mediation, empathy",
          "Innovation and ethical risk-taking in public service"
        ]}
      ]
    }
  ];

  var KEY = 'bharatnotes_upsc_checklist';
  function getState() { try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(KEY) || '{}'); } catch(e) { return {}; } }
  function saveState(s) { localStorage.setItem(KEY, JSON.stringify(s)); }
  var state = getState();

  var totalTopics = 0;
  SYLLABUS.forEach(function(p) { p.sections.forEach(function(s) { totalTopics += s.topics.length; }); });

  var CIRC = 2 * Math.PI * 42; // 263.89

  // ── Paper mini cards ──
  var gridEl = document.getElementById('ck-paper-grid');
  function renderPaperCards() {
    var html = '';
    SYLLABUS.forEach(function(paper) {
      var t = 0, d = 0;
      paper.sections.forEach(function(s) { s.topics.forEach(function(tp) { t++; if (state[paper.id+'/'+s.name+'/'+tp]) d++; }); });
      var pct = t ? Math.round(d/t*100) : 0;
      html += '<div class="ck-paper-card" style="--ck-color:'+paper.color+';" data-paper="'+paper.id+'">';
      html += '<p class="ck-paper-card__title">'+paper.short+'</p>';
      html += '<div class="ck-paper-card__bar"><div class="ck-paper-card__fill" style="width:'+pct+'%;background:'+paper.color+';"></div></div>';
      html += '<div class="ck-paper-card__meta"><span>'+d+'/'+t+'</span><span style="font-weight:700;color:'+paper.color+';">'+pct+'%</span></div>';
      html += '</div>';
    });
    gridEl.innerHTML = html;
  }

  // ── Progress ring ──
  function updateRing() {
    var d = 0;
    SYLLABUS.forEach(function(p) { p.sections.forEach(function(s) { s.topics.forEach(function(t) { if (state[p.id+'/'+s.name+'/'+t]) d++; }); }); });
    var pct = totalTopics ? Math.round(d/totalTopics*100) : 0;
    var offset = CIRC - (pct/100)*CIRC;
    document.getElementById('ck-ring').setAttribute('stroke-dashoffset', offset);
    document.getElementById('ck-ring-pct').textContent = pct+'%';
    document.getElementById('ck-ring-sub').textContent = d+' / '+totalTopics;
    document.getElementById('ck-hero-label').textContent = d+' of '+totalTopics+' topics completed';
    var left = totalTopics - d;
    document.getElementById('ck-hero-sub').textContent = left > 0 ? left+' remaining — keep going!' : 'All topics covered! Revision time.';
  }

  // ── Stage tabs ──
  var activeStage = 'all';
  document.getElementById('ck-stage-tabs').addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    var tab = e.target.closest('.ck-stage-tab');
    if (!tab) return;
    activeStage = tab.dataset.stage;
    document.querySelectorAll('.ck-stage-tab').forEach(function(t) { t.classList.toggle('active', t === tab); });
    renderChecklist();
  });

  // ── Paper card click → filter ──
  gridEl.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    var card = e.target.closest('.ck-paper-card');
    if (!card) return;
    var pid = card.dataset.paper;
    var paper = SYLLABUS.find(function(p) { return p.id === pid; });
    if (paper) {
      activeStage = paper.stage;
      document.querySelectorAll('.ck-stage-tab').forEach(function(t) { t.classList.toggle('active', t.dataset.stage === activeStage); });
      renderChecklist();
      // Scroll to that paper section
      var el = document.querySelector('[data-section-paper="'+pid+'"]');
      if (el) el.scrollIntoView({ behavior:'smooth', block:'start' });
    }
  });

  // ── Render checklist ──
  var listEl = document.getElementById('ck-list');
  function renderChecklist() {
    var search = (document.getElementById('ck-search').value||'').toLowerCase();
    var statusF = document.getElementById('ck-status').value;
    var html = '';

    SYLLABUS.forEach(function(paper) {
      if (activeStage !== 'all' && paper.stage !== activeStage) return;

      var pt = 0, pd = 0;
      paper.sections.forEach(function(s) { s.topics.forEach(function(t) { pt++; if (state[paper.id+'/'+s.name+'/'+t]) pd++; }); });
      var ppct = pt ? Math.round(pd/pt*100) : 0;

      var sectionsHtml = '';
      var hasAny = false;

      paper.sections.forEach(function(sec, si) {
        var topicsHtml = '';
        var st = 0, sd = 0;

        sec.topics.forEach(function(topic) {
          var tid = paper.id+'/'+sec.name+'/'+topic;
          var done = !!state[tid];
          st++; if (done) sd++;

          if (statusF === 'done' && !done) return;
          if (statusF === 'pending' && done) return;
          if (search && topic.toLowerCase().indexOf(search) === -1 && sec.name.toLowerCase().indexOf(search) === -1) return;

          topicsHtml += '<label class="ck-topic'+(done?' ck-topic--done':'')+'" style="--ck-color:'+paper.color+';">';
          topicsHtml += '<input type="checkbox" data-tid="'+tid.replace(/"/g,'&quot;')+'"'+(done?' checked':'')+'>';
          topicsHtml += '<span>'+topic+'</span></label>';
        });

        if (!topicsHtml) return;
        hasAny = true;
        var spct = st ? Math.round(sd/st*100) : 0;

        sectionsHtml += '<div class="ck-section" data-section-id="'+paper.id+'-'+si+'">';
        sectionsHtml += '<div class="ck-section__head" data-toggle="'+paper.id+'-'+si+'">';
        sectionsHtml += '<div class="ck-section__color" style="background:'+paper.color+';"></div>';
        sectionsHtml += '<div class="ck-section__info"><p class="ck-section__title">'+sec.name+'</p>';
        sectionsHtml += '<span class="ck-section__count">'+sd+' / '+st+'</span></div>';
        sectionsHtml += '<span class="ck-section__pct" style="color:'+paper.color+';">'+spct+'%</span>';
        sectionsHtml += '<span class="ck-section__arrow"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>';
        sectionsHtml += '</div>';
        sectionsHtml += '<div class="ck-section__body">'+topicsHtml+'</div></div>';
      });

      if (!hasAny) return;

      html += '<div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-6);" data-section-paper="'+paper.id+'">';
      html += '<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-3);margin-bottom:var(--space-3);">';
      html += '<div style="width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;background:'+paper.color+';flex-shrink:0;"></div>';
      html += '<h3 style="font-size:var(--text-sm);font-weight:700;color:'+paper.color+';margin:0;flex:1;">'+paper.title+'</h3>';
      html += '<span style="font-size:var(--text-xs);font-weight:700;color:'+paper.color+';">'+ppct+'%</span></div>';
      html += sectionsHtml + '</div>';
    });

    listEl.innerHTML = html || '<p style="text-align:center;color:var(--color-text-muted);padding:var(--space-8);">No topics match your filters.</p>';
  }

  function updateAll() { updateRing(); renderPaperCards(); renderChecklist(); }

  // ── Accordion toggle ──
  listEl.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    var head = e.target.closest('.ck-section__head');
    if (!head) return;
    var body = head.nextElementSibling;
    var arrow = head.querySelector('.ck-section__arrow');
    body.classList.toggle('open');
    if (arrow) arrow.classList.toggle('open');
  });

  // ── Checkbox toggle ──
  listEl.addEventListener('change', function(e) {
    if (e.target.type !== 'checkbox') return;
    var tid = e.target.dataset.tid;
    if (e.target.checked) state[tid] = 1; else delete state[tid];
    saveState(state);
    var label = e.target.closest('.ck-topic');
    if (label) label.classList.toggle('ck-topic--done', e.target.checked);
    updateRing(); renderPaperCards();
    // Update section counts without full re-render
    var section = e.target.closest('.ck-section');
    if (section) {
      var checks = section.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');
      var total = checks.length, done = 0;
      checks.forEach(function(c) { if (c.checked) done++; });
      var pct = total ? Math.round(done/total*100) : 0;
      var countEl = section.querySelector('.ck-section__count');
      var pctEl = section.querySelector('.ck-section__pct');
      if (countEl) countEl.textContent = done+' / '+total;
      if (pctEl) pctEl.textContent = pct+'%';
    }
  });

  // ── Search & status filter ──
  var searchTimer;
  document.getElementById('ck-search').addEventListener('input', function() {
    clearTimeout(searchTimer);
    searchTimer = setTimeout(renderChecklist, 200);
  });
  document.getElementById('ck-status').addEventListener('change', renderChecklist);

  // ── Bulk actions ──
  document.getElementById('ck-mark-visible').addEventListener('click', function() {
    var boxes = listEl.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]:not(:checked)');
    boxes.forEach(function(cb) { cb.checked = true; state[cb.dataset.tid] = 1; });
    saveState(state); updateAll();
  });
  document.getElementById('ck-clear-visible').addEventListener('click', function() {
    var boxes = listEl.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]:checked');
    boxes.forEach(function(cb) { cb.checked = false; delete state[cb.dataset.tid]; });
    saveState(state); updateAll();
  });

  // ── Export ──
  document.getElementById('ck-export').addEventListener('click', function() {
    var blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(state, null, 2)], { type:'application/json' });
    var a = document.createElement('a');
    a.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    a.download = 'bharatnotes-upsc-checklist.json';
    a.click(); URL.revokeObjectURL(a.href);
  });

  // ── Import with Comparison ──
  var pendingImport = null;
  var dialog = document.getElementById('ck-import-dialog');

  function computeDiff(imported) {
    var currentKeys = new Set(Object.keys(state));
    var importKeys = new Set(Object.keys(imported));
    var newTopics = [], common = [], onlyCurrent = [];
    importKeys.forEach(function(k) {
      if (currentKeys.has(k)) common.push(k); else newTopics.push(k);
    });
    currentKeys.forEach(function(k) { if (!importKeys.has(k)) onlyCurrent.push(k); });
    return { newTopics: newTopics, common: common, onlyCurrent: onlyCurrent, imported: imported };
  }

  function showDiffDialog(diff) {
    var statsEl = document.getElementById('ck-diff-stats');
    var papersEl = document.getElementById('ck-diff-papers');

    // Summary
    var total = diff.newTopics.length + diff.common.length + diff.onlyCurrent.length;
    statsEl.innerHTML =
      '<div class="ck-stat" style="padding:var(--space-3);"><span class="ck-stat__num" style="color:#047857;">+' + diff.newTopics.length + '</span><span class="ck-stat__label">New from file</span></div>' +
      '<div class="ck-stat" style="padding:var(--space-3);"><span class="ck-stat__num" style="color:var(--color-brand);">' + diff.common.length + '</span><span class="ck-stat__label">Already done</span></div>' +
      '<div class="ck-stat" style="padding:var(--space-3);"><span class="ck-stat__num" style="color:var(--color-accent-hover);">' + diff.onlyCurrent.length + '</span><span class="ck-stat__label">Only in current</span></div>';

    // Per-paper breakdown
    var paperMap = {};
    SYLLABUS.forEach(function(p) { paperMap[p.id] = { title: p.short, color: p.color, added: 0, common: 0, lost: 0 }; });
    function getPaper(key) { return key.split('/')[0]; }
    diff.newTopics.forEach(function(k) { var p = getPaper(k); if (paperMap[p]) paperMap[p].added++; });
    diff.common.forEach(function(k) { var p = getPaper(k); if (paperMap[p]) paperMap[p].common++; });
    diff.onlyCurrent.forEach(function(k) { var p = getPaper(k); if (paperMap[p]) paperMap[p].lost++; });

    var phtml = '<table style="width:100%;font-size:var(--text-xs);border-collapse:collapse;">';
    phtml += '<tr style="border-bottom:2px solid var(--color-border);"><th style="text-align:left;padding:4px 8px;">Paper</th><th style="padding:4px;color:#047857;">+New</th><th style="padding:4px;color:var(--color-brand);">Same</th><th style="padding:4px;color:var(--color-accent-hover);">Only You</th></tr>';
    SYLLABUS.forEach(function(p) {
      var d = paperMap[p.id];
      if (d.added + d.common + d.lost === 0) return;
      phtml += '<tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light, rgba(0,0,0,0.06));">';
      phtml += '<td style="padding:5px 8px;font-weight:600;color:' + d.color + ';">' + d.title + '</td>';
      phtml += '<td style="padding:5px;text-align:center;color:#047857;">' + (d.added || '-') + '</td>';
      phtml += '<td style="padding:5px;text-align:center;">' + (d.common || '-') + '</td>';
      phtml += '<td style="padding:5px;text-align:center;color:var(--color-accent-hover);">' + (d.lost || '-') + '</td>';
      phtml += '</tr>';
    });
    phtml += '</table>';

    if (diff.newTopics.length === 0 && diff.onlyCurrent.length === 0) {
      phtml += '<p style="text-align:center;color:var(--color-text-muted);padding:var(--space-4);font-size:var(--text-sm);">Both files have identical progress.</p>';
    }
    papersEl.innerHTML = phtml;

    if (typeof dialog.showModal === 'function') dialog.showModal();
  }

  document.getElementById('ck-import-btn').addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('ck-import-file').click();
  });
  document.getElementById('ck-import-file').addEventListener('change', function(e) {
    var file = e.target.files[0];
    if (!file) return;
    var reader = new FileReader();
    reader.onload = function(ev) {
      try {
        var imported = JSON.parse(ev.target.result);
        pendingImport = computeDiff(imported);
        showDiffDialog(pendingImport);
      } catch(err) { alert('Invalid file format.'); }
    };
    reader.readAsText(file);
    e.target.value = '';
  });

  // Dialog actions
  document.getElementById('ck-dialog-close').addEventListener('click', function() { dialog.close(); pendingImport = null; });
  document.getElementById('ck-diff-cancel').addEventListener('click', function() { dialog.close(); pendingImport = null; });
  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e) { if (e.target === dialog) { dialog.close(); pendingImport = null; } });

  document.getElementById('ck-diff-merge').addEventListener('click', function() {
    if (!pendingImport) return;
    // Merge: keep current + add new from imported
    pendingImport.newTopics.forEach(function(k) { state[k] = pendingImport.imported[k]; });
    saveState(state); updateAll();
    dialog.close(); pendingImport = null;
  });

  document.getElementById('ck-diff-replace').addEventListener('click', function() {
    if (!pendingImport) return;
    // Replace: discard current, use imported entirely
    state = {};
    Object.keys(pendingImport.imported).forEach(function(k) { state[k] = pendingImport.imported[k]; });
    saveState(state); updateAll();
    dialog.close(); pendingImport = null;
  });

  // ── Reset ──
  document.getElementById('ck-reset').addEventListener('click', function() {
    if (confirm('Reset ALL checklist progress? This cannot be undone.')) {
      state = {}; saveState(state); updateAll();
    }
  });

  // ── Initial render ──
  updateAll();
  // Auto-expand first section of first visible paper
  var firstBody = listEl.querySelector('.ck-section__body');
  var firstArrow = listEl.querySelector('.ck-section__arrow');
  if (firstBody) { firstBody.classList.add('open'); if (firstArrow) firstArrow.classList.add('open'); }
})();
</script>
